Layer 1 — gateway.py call_llm()
  Token budget: 4000 tokens for history
  Action: trim from oldest messages first
  When: every LLM call

Layer 2 — context_manager.py
  Threshold: 80% of 128k context window (~102k tokens)
  Action: summarize old messages into one paragraph,
          keep last 6 messages verbatim
  When: before node_generate_response if messages are long

Layer 3 — kiotel_chatbot/main.py session store
  Limit: 30 messages (15 turns) per session
  Action: sliding window, oldest dropped
  When: after every chat response


What happens at 80% context:

20 messages exist → context_manager detects 80%+ used
    → summarize messages 1-14 into ~150 word paragraph
    → keep messages 15-20 verbatim
    → inject summary into system prompt:
      "--- CONVERSATION SUMMARY (earlier context) ---
       User asked about X, assistant explained Y...
       ---"
    → LLM gets full context without token overflow